cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "This benchmark is pre-release and has no tagged version yet. A version field and date-released will be added when the first public release is tagged as v1."
title: "Wearable Assistant Context Benchmark"
abstract: "Product benchmark for comparing models on cross-turn reference resolution under context change in a wearable multimodal assistant. Built from real user feedback and product testing to support a practical model-selection decision. The pre-release bank contains 101 scenarios and represents spoken user queries through transcript proxies."
authors:
  - family-names: "Dryer"
    given-names: "Nate"
repository-code: "https://github.com/n-dryer/wearable-assistant-context-bench"
url: "https://github.com/n-dryer/wearable-assistant-context-bench"
keywords:
  - product benchmark
  - wearable multimodal assistant
  - reference resolution
  - context change
  - model selection
  - context shift
  - LLM-as-judge
